assertList

protected <X> boolean assertList(String propertyName,
                                 AssertReportBuilder report,
                                 List<X> expected,
                                 List<X> actual,
                                 List<IProperty> properties,
                                 NodesList nodesList,
                                 boolean isProperty)
Handles list asserting. It traverses trough the list by list index start from 0 and going up to list size and asserts every two elements on matching index. Lists cannot be asserted if their sizes are different.

Type Parameters:
X - object type
Parameters:
propertyName - name of current property
report - assert report builder
expected - expected list
actual - actual list
properties - list of excluded properties
nodesList - list of object that had been asserted
isProperty - is it parent object or its member
Returns:
- true if every element from expected list with index i is asserted with element from actual list with index i, false otherwise.
